{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["57-PHM-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"PHM"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Philemon \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Paul’s Letter to Philemon \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Philemon \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Phm \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Paul’s Letter to Philemon \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"PHM 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"PHM 1:1"},"Paul, a prisoner of Masih Isa, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our beloved fellow worker,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"PHM 1:2"},"to the beloved Apphia, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the assembly in your house:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"PHM 1:3"},"Grace to you and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"PHM 1:4"},"I thank my Allah always, making mention of you in my prayers,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"PHM 1:5"},"hearing of your love and of the faith which you have towards the Lord Isa, and towards all the saints,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"PHM 1:6"},"that the fellowship of your faith may become effective in the knowledge of every good thing which is in us in Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"PHM 1:7"},"For we have much joy and comfort in your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"PHM 1:8"},"Therefore though I have all boldness in Masih to command you that which is appropriate,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"PHM 1:9"},"yet for love’s sake I rather beg, being such a one as Paul, the aged, but also a prisoner of Al Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"PHM 1:10"},"I beg you for my child, whom I have become the father of in my chains, Onesimus,\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Onesimus means “useful”."]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"PHM 1:11"},"who once was useless to you, but now is useful to you and to me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"PHM 1:12"},"I am sending him back. Therefore receive him, that is, my own heart,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"PHM 1:13"},"whom I desired to keep with me, that on your behalf he might serve me in my chains for the Good News.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"PHM 1:14"},"But I was willing to do nothing without your consent, that your goodness would not be as of necessity, but of free will.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"PHM 1:15"},"For perhaps he was therefore separated from you for a while, that you would have him forever,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"PHM 1:16"},"no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a beloved brother, especially to me, but how much rather to you, both in the\nflesh and in the Lord. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"PHM 1:17"},"If then you count me a partner, receive him as you would receive me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"PHM 1:18"},"But if he has wronged you at all or owes you anything, put that to my account.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"PHM 1:19"},"I, Paul, write this with my own hand: I will repay it (not to mention to you that you owe to me even your own self\nbesides). \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"PHM 1:20"},"Yes, brother, let me have joy from you in the Lord. Refresh my heart in the Lord.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"PHM 1:21"},"Having confidence in your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even beyond what I say.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"PHM 1:22"},"Also, prepare a guest room for me, for I hope that through your prayers I will be restored to you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"PHM 1:23"},"Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Masih Isa, greets you, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"PHM 1:24"},"as do Marqus, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luqa, my fellow workers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"PHM 1:25"},"The grace of our Lord Al Masih Isa be with your spirit. Amen.\n"]}]}